// SKIP: The Q&A asks whether any spells grant long rest benefits without a full rest — the accepted answer is "possibly Wish, at DM's discretion." The spec models long rest mechanics (`pLongRest`, `pRestoreAllSlots`) but has no model of Wish, Catnap, or any spell that bypasses the rest duration requirement. The core ruling is DM-fiat, not a deterministic mechanical rule encodable against the spec.